# Yoni Repository Structure

## Durable source (recoverable without generated code)

- `yoni.config.yoni`, `.yoni/`, `project/`, `domains/`, `capabilities/`, `views/`, `deployments/`, `migrations/`

## Disposable output

- `generated/` — code, docs, tests, infra, ui
- `.ai/` — cache, traces, runs

## Canonical folders (one block, one home)

| Block | Path |
|-------|------|
| project | `project/` |
| domain | `domains/<name>/domain.yoni` |
| entity | `domains/<name>/entities/` |
| intent | `domains/<name>/intents/` |
| rule | `domains/<name>/rules/` |
| query | `domains/<name>/queries/` |
| action | `domains/<name>/actions/` |
| event | `domains/<name>/events/` |
| state | `domains/<name>/states/` |
| workflow | `domains/<name>/workflows/` |
| constraint | `domains/<name>/constraints/` |
| error | `domains/<name>/errors/` |
| test | `domains/<name>/tests/` |
| capability | `capabilities/<name>/capability.yoni` |
| view | `views/` |
| deployment | `deployments/` |
| migration | `migrations/` |

No `misc/`, `common/`, or `utils/` folders. No duplicate block homes.

## `.yoni/` machine layer

- `conventions/` — naming, IDs, references, lint policy
- `prompts/` — generation, repair, migration, test-generation contracts
- `policies/` — determinism, traceability, security, review
- `schemas/` — blocks, folder-map, file-kinds
